{
  "id": "expert-birdf",
  "title": "birdf",
  "description": "Create a 2D interactive slingshot ball launch game with Angry Birds-style mechanics. The game features a SlingShot_Manager script that handles touch-based slingshot controls, ball launching physics, and obstacle interaction. Players pull the grabbable ball (connected to front/back slingshot straps) to set launch trajectory, release to shoot with physics-based velocity (maxLaunchSpeed: 15), and aim at obstacles and collectibles. The game includes scoring, camera following, and touch detection with configurable settings like invertTouchY and autoDetectTouchY. The slingshot system uses strap attachment points and drag radius detection for natural pulling mechanics. [source: birdf.json]",
